Subject: [PATCH] {MAYBE UPS} fs/splice: initialize ret

If iter_file_splice_write is called with len = 0, it returns an
unitialized value. In practice, callers such as splice syscall ensures
that len != 0, but it does not hurt to add an extra layer.
---
 fs/splice.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/fs/splice.c b/fs/splice.c
index b3daa971f597..446ee1dcf334 100644
--- a/fs/splice.c
+++ b/fs/splice.c
@@ -692,7 +692,7 @@ iter_file_splice_write(struct pipe_inode_info *pipe, struct file *out,
 	int nbufs = pipe->buffers;
 	struct bio_vec *array = kcalloc(nbufs, sizeof(struct bio_vec),
 					GFP_KERNEL);
-	ssize_t ret;
+	ssize_t ret = 0;
 
 	if (unlikely(!array))
 		return -ENOMEM;
